			<tr>
				<td colspan="2"><span class="postbody">Easy, you make a spell set with the spells you want, then the command is (I think)
<br />

<br />
/loadspellset spellsetname
<br />

<br />
So, lets say you want dooming darkness and root to share spell slot 8. Make 2 spell sets:  Lets call the first one "aggro kite" and the second one "root".
<br />

<br />
Load all of your normal aggro kite spells including dooming darkness in slot 8. Save that spell set as "aggro kite"
<br />

<br />
Unmem all 8 slots, then mem only root in slot 8. Save that spell slot as "root".
<br />

<br />
Now make 2 hotkeys, one will be "loadspellset aggro kite" and the other will be "loadspellset root".
<br />

<br />
Voila, you can use the 2 hotkeys to swap slot 8.
<br />

<br />

<br />
On the use of Scent of Terris. I'm not convinced this is efficient. Ignite blood has a -100 resist mod on it, so it doesn't need a debuff. So it's used only for Cessation of Cor, Envenomed Bolt and Plague. I guess if it saves you one resist, it has paid for itself. But would you normally get at least one resist on every mob? And then you have to figure in that Scent of Terris is just as likely to be resisted as those other spells.</span><span class="gensmall"></span></td>
			</tr>
