			<tr>
				<td colspan="2"><span class="postbody">Over the course of a 20 gargoyle session I will guarantee 100% that casting scent of terris will net you mana. I've had as many as 7 resists in one fight, and then 3 fights in a row with no resists. To each his own, however. Some people would cast ignite and splurt and just run the mofo's for 10 minutes, heh. I spose someone could parse and all that crap if they REEAALLY cared but I sure don't. Here's what I foresee of  Joe_Newb_to_the_garg_spot's reading this. He's gonna  kill a few without using scent and it's going to go fine. He'll get a resist or 2 but be of the mindset that Scare is full of shit. Then he's going to get that mystical magical Weathered Gargoyle that's gonna resist 7 times and eat his manapool. During the 5 minutes of downtime Joe is gonna build his ass some spell swapping macro's just out of boredom and curiosity. The he's going to use them and discover it's less frustrating to just cast the damn debuff. Then the novelty of spellswapping hotkeys will wear thin and he'll stop. Then Mister-MR gargy will pop again and kill his mana pool and Joe's gonna be sitting there behind the keyboard with a smoke completely burned to the nub and stinking up the room shouting "FUCKYOUMOTHAFUCKINPIECOSHITGARGOYLRESITINGMOTHERFUCKER!" and go back to using the buttons again. Just a feeling, I could be wrong.
<br />

<br />
I prefer to throw the kitchen sink at mobs killing a few fast, and then resting afterward. That's the joy (and curse) of the garg spot. The upside is, you can take as long as you want with no pressure to keep a spawn cycle hammered down. The downside is, it gets old pretty quick. I find myself letting manaskin drop and attempting to channel root after awhile instead of doing it right. I've even done 2 at a time and almost dieing rather than just swapping in coma and starting over. The biggest danger in the garg spot isn't the gargs, but complacency.<br />_________________<br /><img src="http://home.comcast.net/~drdeathbane/images/scarecroweIV.gif" border="0" />
