			<tr>
				<td colspan="2"><span class="postbody">I can see how scent might work for you.
<br />

<br />
I'm more of an efficiency nut. I try to do my fights in such a way that I end up with as much mana at the end as I had at the beginning. That means longer fights and letting the pet do more of the work.
<br />

<br />
So, I'll be relying more on the more efficient Splurt and Ignite Blood which are both very low resist. I'll probably keep CoC on, too, since that not only does damage, it lowers AC and helps my pet do damage. But casting a 200 mana debuff just for CoC doesn't seem worth it. I also wouldn't try to cast CoC 7 times. After the second resist I would just give up on it.
<br />

<br />
Now if Scent was also a MR debuff, I'd do it just to avoid darkness resists, but that's for safety, not efficency.</span><span class="gensmall"></span></td>
			</tr>
